    <text type="letter"> 
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.03704.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                <handShift rend="printed"/> 
                <name type="place">FREDERICK A. STOKES, Successor to<lb/>WHITE, STOKES, &#38; ALLEN,<lb/>PUBLISHERS, STATIONERS, AND IMPORTERS,</name>
                <name type="place"> 182 Fifth Avenue, New York.</name>
                <date when="1887-04-30"><handShift rend="printed"/>April 30th, 1887.</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute><handShift rend="printed"/>Mr. Walt Whitman:</salute>
                <salute><handShift rend="printed"/>328 Mickle St., Camden,
                        N.J.</salute>
                  <salute><handShift rend="printed"/>Dear Sir:</salute>
            </opener>
            <p><handShift rend="printed"/>I have your kind card of the 29th inst.,<ptr
                    target="loc.03704_n2"/> and in reply would say that you are indebted entirely to
                Mr. Browne for the copy of 'Bugle Echoes' which you have received. </p>
            <p><handShift rend="printed"/>I take pleasure in forwarding the card to him as you request, also in saying that in
                case you desire another copy of the book for any purpose, I shall feel honored if
                you will allow me to send it to you with my compliments. </p>
            <closer>
                <salute><handShift rend="printed"/>Very truly yours,</salute>
                <signed><handShift rend="manuscript"/>Frederick A. Stokes</signed>
            </closer>
            <note type="authorial" place="inline"><handShift rend="printed"/>Dictated.</note>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.03704.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
    </text>
